Hi Janina,
Thanks for the update.
Regarding accessibility, yes of course. When we go live, we will move it over as it can only be active on the live domain.
Regarding the RRPH pages, yes this makes sense. It will work best if I can request a content freeze on the live https://royalrehab.com.au/ site. We will then update the RRPH pages to replace the purples with the yellows/oranges on the staging server. Additionally the header on https://royalrehab.com.au/ needs to be updated to have the new site switcher enabling users to jump from one site to another. Once approved we will 'push' the staging server updates to the live site and the content freeze will be lifted. Does this work for you? FYI, the content freeze will be 1 day for us to make the changes + the time required for you to review and approved. This is fine - just want to double check this does not impact people visiting the website? Only the changes? Also, just want to confirm this will be a draft website and not go live until approval?
Also, it sounds like there are no further changes at this stage for Metro? We are presenting this to our CEO shortly so at this stage, no further edits on your end required but I'll keep you posted. We are almost there!!
Thanks and speak soon,

Heath Maguire
CREATIVE DIRECTOR

Phone: 1300 072 134
Mobile: 0415 162 271
Email: heath@wolfiq.com.au
